OL,3,CNoah Donohoe inquest told storm drain
OL,4,C'could be easily opened'
OL,6,FThe jury at the inquest into the death
OL,7,Fof Noah Donohoe has been told that the
OL,8,Fculvert in the area where he
OL,9,Fdisappeared was "unlocked and could be
OL,10,Feasily opened".
OL,12,FNoah, a pupil of St Malachy's College,
OL,13,Fwas 14 when his naked body was found
OL,14,Fin a storm drain tunnel in north
OL,15,FBelfast in June 2020, six days after
OL,16,Fleaving home on his bike to meet two
OL,17,Ffriends in the Cavehill area of the
OL,18,Fcity.
OL,20,FA post-mortem examination found the
OL,21,Fcause of death was drowning.
OL,26,@qD@QOUrD@NO]
